The paper proposes an algorithm for detecting communities of links in networks, which is a common topic in several sub-categories of computer science. The use of a memetic algorithm suggests a focus on optimization and search algorithms, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The evaluation function and the focus on local information suggest a potential connection to sub-categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of probabilistic evolutionary strategies and deterministic local searches suggests a potential connection to sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
